{
  "title": "Containerizing REST APIs with FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to create and containerize a REST API using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+. This tutorial demonstrates the use of Docker Compose for orchestration.",
  "key_points": [
    "Prerequisites: Python 3.12+, FastAPI, Uvicorn ASGI server (FastAPI's recommended ASGI server), and Docker with Docker Compose",
    "Install the required dependencies using pip",
    "Create a FastAPI application",
    "Dockerize your FastAPI app by creating a Dockerfile",
    "Build the Docker image",
    "Define services, volumes, and networks in a docker-compose.yml file for the app and Uvicorn ASGI server",
    "Start both containers with a single command using `docker-compose up`"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "bash",
      "code": "pip install fastapi uvicorn"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n\ndef get_root():\n    return {'Hello': 'World'}\napp.get('/')(get_root)"
    },
    {
      "language": "Dockerfile",
      "code": "FROM python:3.12-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY . .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\nCMD [\"uvicorn\", \"main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"8000\"]"
    },
    {
      "language": "yaml",
      "code": "\nversion: '3'\nservices:\n  app:\n    build:\n      context: .\n    ports:\n      - '8000:8000'\n    command: uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "This guide is tailored for Python 3.12+ and FastAPI version 0.74.0."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Always ensure you have the latest versions of Docker and Docker Compose installed.",
    "Adjust your application's ports as needed in both the Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml file."
  ]
}

code_examples.code:
from fastapi import FastAPI
app = FastAPI()

def get_root():
    return {'Hello': 'World'}
app.get('/')(get_root)
